rComments: Shes very kind and caring and SUPER knowledgeable. You can tell how much she loves this topic by the way she teaches it. Shes accessible outside of class (gives her home phone number!!) and cares about your mark. Others on here say she is a hard marker but I didn't find that.

Amazing professor, she made me fall in love with history again. Reminds me of my grade 6 teacher who made me love history in the first place. She is a tough marker, but if you do the work you will do well. Biggest tip is get her to know who you are. Do the readings, talk in class and take advantage of her office hours. She also has the best stories

Excellent professor. Tough marker? Yes. Though, if you put in hard work and go to lectures engaged, you will do  well. Useful tips for Dr. Hatton's courses: *listen*, proof-read, and take advantage of office hours. Listening to lectures is key. She will not work from the text as she knows the content like the back of her hand.
Approachable and ever so knowledgeable!

She's the reason I made history my major! She is the most dedicated prof I've ever had. The people who gave her a bad rating are insane! As long as you do your work and ask questions you will get a good grade. You can't skate by, you have to work for it! She even meets with students to help with papers. I'm much better at essays because of her!  A+
A great prof! Extremely helpful and understanding.
She is a tough marker, so unless you can't find any other 4th year course to take,drop this one.  And her lectures are such a yawnnn.
Don't be fooled by how nice she is, she is a veryyyy hard marker!!!  If you get a 70 consider yourself lucky!
Such a hard marker!  Pray that you get the TA to mark yours, and if it's a 4th year course than you're screwed since it's just her.

Amazing prof, very sweet, very willing to help out. Very generous with marks on exams. As long as you follow along in lectures, you'll be fine, she pauses for questions so don't be scared to ask her to clarify!

Awesome prof. This was my first history course, and she made it super easy for me.  She REALLY cares about students and despite her age goes above and beyond to help them out. You can send her a one sentence email and she will type a 3 paragraph answer for you - thats the dedication she has. Shes in a league of her own. She made me love history.

She is the cutest and nicest professor ever!!!! I absolutely love her!!! It is not a bird course, you really gotta read and listen to her during lectures, BUT you end up knowing A LOT of history!!! VERY APPROACHABLE and just an amazing woman!!! I definitely recommend anyone interested in history to take her classes!!
Best professor
dropped the class she is boring teacher but is the sweetest women

AMAZING!! She is sweet and very dedicated to her students. She even gave the entire class a last minute extention on our essay because she felt it was in everyones best interest. She is the best and most approachable professor I have ever had. I mean what other professor do you know that gives out their home phone number so they can help more?
She is really nice, but it's not a bird course!  You need to work for the marks.
Fantastic professor. Very nice, helpful, and knowledgeable.

This woman is the cutest and warmest person I have ever known. She is an absolute gem! Her lectures are insightful and her course is straightforward and completely doable. Her choice of TA's are iffy. But the course is amazing, great subject matter, interesting texts and presented in a fascinating form. It's a shame she doesn't teach more courses.

If you go to class every class you'll be fine she's adorable and absolutely a gem for help. She was very thorough and very approachable to ask questions. I would recommend this class. study hard and read your notes over throroughly before mid term and final.

She is an awesome prof, very smart and knowledgable about her field but - I honestly couldn't understand hwat my TA was talking about. Ever. And the tests are based very heavily on the tutorials, so I didn't do well. Just make sure you get one of the good TAs!

I loved Professor Hatton!  She is really experienced with the material and teaching and the lectures are clearly planned out.  It's easy to take notes and the test and exam formats are very fair.  If you put a little effort into this class, you're assured a good mark.  Just hope that you get a TA to mark your paper instead of her...!
Excellent, funny and thorough. I think she provides an excellent introduction to the subject. Paige the TA was brilliant (and hot)and made the tutorials very productive.

She's one of the most brilliant women I know. She knows her stuff from top to bottom and always has interesting anecdotes. Shes fairly honest and straightforward and you know what to expect from her. If you do not like honesty, then dont take her courses
She's so hot- I love this lady... she's like a funny grandma
Very biased and rude...
don't bother going to class, just read the textbook and you'll be fine, puts up words up on the board, know those and you're fine

I enjoyed professor Hatton's classes. Her narratives about European history are so vivid and really nice to listen to. However, she is a tough marker. She expects superior understanding of the matter for "B". I wonder if she ever gave someone "A".
No Comments
Fantastic class and teacher! One of the best!
